## D6. No-legacy-IDW-fallback structural argument
# The §2.4 smoke does not itself invoke the forcing producer or the shud_runtime stager against the
# evidence identity (per §2.4 non-goal "no basin migration and no production .sp.att rewrite"). The
# no-IDW-fallback guarantee for the evidence identity is proven by three independent layers of code:
#
# Layer 1 — scheduler dispatch filter (services/orchestrator/chain_repository.py:260-271):
#   list_forecast_model_ids SELECTs from core.model_instance WHERE active_flag = true AND lifecycle_state = 'active'.
#   The §2.3 D3 evidence row has active_flag=false AND lifecycle_state='inactive' -> DOUBLE-EXCLUDED.
#   The scheduler cannot dispatch a forecast cycle against the evidence identity.
#
# Layer 2 — producer station loader filter (workers/forcing_producer/store.py:73-93):
#   load_met_stations SELECTs met.met_station WHERE active_flag = true AND station_role <> DIRECT_GRID_CACHE_STATION_ROLE
#     AND NOT properties_json @> '{"derived_cache":true}' AND COALESCE(properties_json->>'forcing_mapping_mode','') <> 'direct_grid'.
#   The 3 evidence mirror rows have active_flag=false + station_role='forcing_proxy' -> ALSO DOUBLE-EXCLUDED
#     (active_flag AND station_role gates both fail on active_flag=false).
#   Even if the scheduler were bypassed, the producer cannot enumerate evidence mirrors as stations to
#   produce forcing for.
#
# Layer 3 — runtime path selection (workers/shud_runtime/runtime.py):
#   The direct-grid staging path _read_direct_grid_forcing_member_bytes (:1179, :1195) is selected when
#   the model_instance's resource_profile.direct_grid_forcing block is present. §2.4 D2 SELECT confirms
#   the evidence row carries this block with forcing_mapping_mode='direct_grid'. Therefore, if any
#   pipeline hypothetically reached the runtime with this identity, staging would take the direct-grid
#   path -- never legacy IDW.
#
# Composite: layers 1 + 2 prove the evidence identity is unreachable by production dispatch/production
# station enumeration; layer 3 proves the residual reachable path (were layers 1-2 bypassed) is
# direct-grid, not IDW. The three layers together supply the no-legacy-IDW-fallback proof required
# by §2.4 without executing a live pipeline pass against the evidence identity (which is out of
# §2.4 scope per non-goal wording).

## D7. Cleanup decision — verifiable confinement (design.md §"Isolation and cleanup")
# Design.md admits two termination paths for smoke-derived rows: (a) remove after evidence capture,
# or (b) verifiably remain confined to the inactive dedicated identity. §2.4 exercises path (b):
# - The §2.3 D3 rows survive the §2.4 audit window with active_flag=false intact (INV.A/C/D/E/F all PASS).
# - The evidence identity is unreachable by both scheduler dispatch and producer station enumeration
#   (D6 layers 1+2 structural argument).
# - The display MVT source layer cannot surface the evidence identity because its active_flag=true gate
#   eliminates all 3 mirror rows (D5 SIM queries).
# - No new rows are inserted during the §2.4 audit window (INV.B basin_version count = 1, unchanged).
# - D4' fresh-window SERIALIZABLE re-attest bounds identity drift across §2.3 D3 -> §2.4 D4 -> D4'
#   with md5-hashed sorted-id lists + total-count net-INSERT bounds.
# Path (b) chosen: the §2.3 D3 rows REMAIN as evidence-only, awaiting §3.1 evidence-package assembly
# and §3.2 openspec validate.
#
# Cleanup-tracking honesty (added §2.4 Round 2 fix for C7):
# The earlier wording "tracked as a §3-time cleanup" overreached: tasks.md §3.1 (line 51-54) and
# §3.2 (line 55-59) contain zero cleanup/DELETE/retire/retirement obligations — §3.1 is about
# evidence-package indexing + cross-artifact consistency, and §3.2 is `openspec validate --strict`
# + `openspec status 3/3` + `ruff check`. Neither section fails if the §2.3 D3 rows persist.
# So the retirement is NOT tracked in this change; it is an EXPLICIT deferral. The correct current
# status is:
#   * The §2.3 D3 registered rows (1 basin, 1 basin_version, 1 river_network_version, 1 model_instance,
#     3 met_station mirrors) REMAIN on node-27 primary PG as evidence-only after §3.2 certification.
#   * Confinement is guaranteed structurally by D6 layers 1+2 (chain_repository + producer filters
#     both exclude active_flag=false rows) plus the display MVT active_flag=true gate (D5). This is
#     defense-in-depth: any future code change that weakens layer 1 or 2 would need to also
#     evade the display gate to reach production surface.
#   * The DELETE ROLLBACK recipe for retirement lives at db-registration-2.3.node-27.pass.log:128-134
#     (5 DELETE statements + POSTCHECK that production 13 model_instance / 13 basin / 6290 met_station
#     counts survive). A future evidence-set retirement change (out of this change's scope) can
#     execute that recipe against the evidence identity when the P0.2 gate is retired.
#   * No follow-on issue is tracked as of §2.4 pass-log capture; a follow-on Epic #886 close pass
#     (or later retirement change) can file one.

